a.

 1. $\nu^{-1}\left((\gamma, \infty)\right) \in \nu^*$.

 2. $\{\mathbf{0}\} \in \sigma(\nu^*)$.

 3. $\mathcal{F} \subseteq \mathcal{A}$.

 4. For every $t \in (0,\infty)$, $\{\tau_0 \leq t\} = \{X_0 = \mathbf{0}\}$.

 5. $\Omega_0 = \{X_0 = \mathbf{0}\}$.

 6. $\Omega_0 = \{\tau_0 = 0\}$.

 7. $\tau_0$ is a $\Phi^{\sigma(\nu^*)}(X)$-stopping time.

 8. $\tau_0$ is $\mathcal{F}/\overline{\mathcal{B}}$-measurable.

 9. For every $t \in [0,\infty)$, $\Omega_0 \in \Phi^{\sigma(\nu^*)}_t(X)$.

 10. $P(\Omega_0) = 1$.

 11. $\mathcal{F}^{\langle 0\rangle} \subseteq \mathcal{F}$.

 12. $\mathcal{F}^{\langle 0\rangle}$ is a $\sigma$-algebra on $\Omega_0$.

 13. $\tau_0^{(0)} = 0$.

 14. $X^{\langle 0\rangle}_{\tau_0^{(0)}} = X_0^{(0)} = \mathbf{0}$.

 15. $\tau_0 \leq \tau_1$.

 16. For every $t \in (0,\infty)$, $\{\tau_1 \leq t\} \subseteq \Omega_0$.

 17. For every $t \in (0,\infty]$, $\{\tau_1 < t\} = \{\tau_1^{(0)} < t\}$.

 18. For every $t \in (0,\infty)$, $\{\tau_1 \leq t\} = \{\tau_1^{(0)} \leq t\}$.

 19. $\tau_1^{(0)} = \inf \left\{t \in [0,\infty)\ |\!:\ \nu\left(X_t^{(0)}\right) > \gamma\right\}$.

 20. $\tau_1^{(0)}$ is a weak $\Phi^{\sigma(\nu^*)}\left(X^{\langle 0\rangle}\right)$-stopping time.

 21. $\tau_1$ is a weak $\Phi^{\sigma(\nu^*)}(X)$-stopping time.

 22. $\tau_1$ is $\mathcal{F}/\overline{\mathcal{B}}$-measurable.

 23. $\Omega_1 \in \mathcal{F}$.

 *** 24. For every $t \in [0,\infty)$, $X_t$ is $\mathcal{F}/\sigma(\nu^*)$-measurable.

 *** 25. For every $s, t \in [0,\infty)$, $X_t - X_s$ is $\mathcal{F}/\sigma(\nu^*)$-measurable.

 *** 26. For every $t \in [0,\infty)$, $\nu\circ X_t$ is $\mathcal{F}/\mathcal{B}$-measurable.

 *** 27. For every $s, t \in [0,\infty)$, $\nu\circ(X_t - X_s)$ is $\mathcal{F}/\mathcal{B}$-measurable.

 28. $P(\Omega_1) = 1$.
